-- Bank of Canada Lends C$125 Million of Securities for One Day
-- B y   C h r i s   F o u r n i e r
-- 2013-02-21T16:32:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-21/bank-of-canada-lends-c-125-million-of-securities-for-one-day.html
The Bank of Canada made C$125
million ($123 million) in one-day loans of securities, under a
program that aims to boost the supply of  government bonds  and
treasury bills in the market when demand is high.  The Ottawa-based central bank announced the loan, which
follows similar lending the previous two days, on its website
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Fournier in Ottawa at 
